==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rejoint
<hw>Re*joint"</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧-joint")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To reunite the joints of; to joint anew.</def>
<rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, to fill up the
joints of, as stones in buildings when the mortar has been dislodged by
age and the action of the weather.</def> <rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1213 --></p>

<p><ent>Rejolt</ent>⟦br⟧
